@prophittcorey Although it works, the stroke color is fixed to what you predefine on the style. I will suggest this one:

```CSS
.fa-outlined {
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent !important;
  -webkit-text-stroke-width: 1px !important;
  -webkit-text-stroke-color: inherit !important;
}
```
Now your font color will be used as stoke color. This gives you more flexibility. For today, I can confirm it works on Chrome and Firefox and Edge even with that prefix!! I cannot confirm if this works on Safari, maybe somebody with a mac or iphone could test.

